{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/2018-11-24-knave-devices/","webpackCompilationHash":"6b11de871cba742ef903","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"htmlAst":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"I've been running a game using rules derived from the "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"http://goblinpunch.blogspot.com/2016/05/the-glog.html"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"GLOG"}]},{"type":"text","value":", but without class templates. The goal of my house rules are to make character creation very fast and completely randomizable. "}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"These are the rules I've been using to re-introduce spells, in a manner inspired by "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://www.drivethrurpg.com/product/250888/Knave"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Knave's"}]},{"type":"text","value":" spell-as-items. They're basically a straight copy-paste of the GLOG "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/0BxVHEMMjLlZ4UWYzX3o1UnEtd0U/view"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"spell-casting rules"}]},{"type":"text","value":". The only changes are re-contextualising them as a physical object instead of a spell, and some additional rules for levelless casting and improving the devices."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h1","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Devices"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Devices are ancient artefacts that possess great power. They act as spells, providing the wielder with extraordinary abilities."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h2","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Device Tier"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Devices have a tier of 1-4. This is the device’s base level of power."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h2","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Using a Device"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Devices have an ability, which relies on charges. A Device has a base number of Charge Dice equal to its tier, and you roll these when you use the device. The more dice rolled, the more powerful the effect."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"When you use a Device, roll a number of d6’s equal to the Device’s current Charge Dice. The ability of the device will depend on the number of [dice] and/or [sum] of values rolled."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Charge Dice rolled with a value of 1-3 are returned to the the Device’s charge pool and can be re-used. Dice of value 4-6 are expended, and don’t return to the device until it is recharged."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h2","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Recharging a device"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"To recharge a Device, expend a charge cell. This resets the Device’s Charge Dice to equal its tier, and takes a number of hours equal to its tier."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h3","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Overcharging"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"When you charge a Device you may spend additional charge cells, one for one, to add "},{"type":"element","tagName":"strong","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Overcharge Dice"}]},{"type":"text","value":" to the Device. These count as extra Charge Dice the next time the Device is used, but are always expended (roll separately or use a different colour from regular charge dice)."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h2","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Device safety"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"A Device can only be safely wielded by a user of equal or greater level than the Device’s tier."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"If you use a device of greater tier than your level, roll "},{"type":"element","tagName":"strong","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"danger dice"}]},{"type":"text","value":" equal to the difference between the values. These do not count towards the device’s effect, but count towards doubles or triples rolled for mishaps and disasters."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"blockquote","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Example: Rolf, a level 1 character, attempts to use a tier two "},{"type":"element","tagName":"strong","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Pusher"}]},{"type":"text","value":". He rolls two "},{"type":"element","tagName":"strong","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"charge dice"}]},{"type":"text","value":" and one "},{"type":"element","tagName":"strong","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"danger die"}]},{"type":"text","value":". The charge dice come up 5 & 3, and a 3 is rolled on the danger die, for a total [sum] of 8 and [dice] of 2. The 3 returns to the device’s charge pool and the 5 is expended. The device also has a Mishap, so Rolf rolls for that before resolving the devices effect."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h2","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Mishaps and disasters"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"When you roll doubles when using a device, it causes a Mishap. When triples (or more) are rolled, it causes a Disaster. Roll on the following tables for the effects."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"div","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"table-roller","properties":{"table":"mishaps,disasters","buttons":"[[\"Random Mishap\", {\n    \"Mishap\": \"d6:Mishap Effect\"\n}], [\"Random Disaster\", {\n    \"Disaster\": \"d4:Disaster Effect\"\n}]]"},"children":[]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h3","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Mishaps"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"div","properties":{"dataTableMarker":"mishaps"},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"table","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"thead","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"tr","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"th","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"d6"}]},{"type":"element","tagName":"th","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Mishap Effect"}]}]}]},{"type":"element","tagName":"tbody","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"tr","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"td","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"1"}]},{"type":"element","tagName":"td","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"All of the Device’s charges are expended"}]}]},{"type":"element","tagName":"tr","properties":{},"children"